This paper proposes a method for Human-Object Interaction (HOI) detection using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method also involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method also involves real-time processing, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the method involves the use of a new dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
